<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/style.css' />
    <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/2.1.3/jquery.min.js"></script>
  </head>
  <body>

    <div class="upperheader">
        <h1><%= title %></h1>
        <p>Hi, Welcome to this study!</p>

    </div>
    <div class="introtext">
        <br>
        <p align="justify">In this study you are going to assume the role of an emergency responder. You will collaborate with a partner and come up with plans for fictional emergency response scenarios. In order to complete the study and receive compensation, you <strong>must</strong>:</p>
        <div>
        <br>
        <ul>
            <li>First, agree to the study consent form.</li>
            <li>Scenario 1</li>
                <br>
                <ul>
                <li>Read the scenario description (5 min timed)</li>
                <li>Engage in text chat with your partner and form a plan (20 min timed)</li>
                <li>Report the plan your team has agreed to (5 min timed)</li>
                </ul>
            <li>Scenario 2</li>
                <br>
                <ul>
                <li>Read the scenario description (5 min timed)</li>
                <li>Engage in text chat with your partner and form a plan (20 min timed)</li>
                <li>Report the plan your team has agreed to (5 min timed)</li>
                </ul>
            <h3>After Planning</h3>
            <li>Complete a post-study questionnaire.</li>
            <li>Complete and email a signed "Payment for Human Subject Testing Form."</li>
        </ul>
        </div>
        <p align="justify">Entire study will take about 65-75 min.  Upon successful completion (quality data, all instructions followed), you will be awarded $15 (check sent from MIT).  There will be 1st and 2nd place prizes to top two teams that come up with "best" plans (feasible and efficient in terms of planning metrics), with each participant paid extra +$25 and +$20. 
    </div>

    <div class="styledbutton" id="timewarning">
      <a href="/consentform"><button>Proceed</button></a>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>











